  <front>
   <head>Epigrammi - LIX. De eodem ad vesperas.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1">
     <l n="1">Audiat surgens pariter, cadensque</l>
     <l n="2">Sol tuas laudes, meritosque honores.</l>
     <l n="3">Urbis o nostrae columen, tuaeque</l>
     <l n="4">Gloria gentis.</l>
     <l n="5">Audiat caelum, mare, terra, et aÃ«r,</l>
     <l n="6">Annuos ritus tibi dum novamus,</l>
     <l n="7">Dum damus flammis adolenda sacris</l>
     <l n="8">Tura per aras.</l>
     <l n="9">Huc ades festa redimite fronde,</l>
     <l n="10">Caelitum plausus, choreasque linquens;</l>
     <l n="11">Et tuam sedem, tua, Gaudiose,</l>
     <l n="12">Ossa revise;</l>
     <l n="13">Ossa, quae longa tumuli sub umbra</l>
     <l n="14">Abdita, ignaras latuere gentes;</l>
     <l n="15">Nocte mox pulsa redeunt apertas</l>
     <l n="16">Lucis in auras.</l>
     <l n="17">Hic dies nobis celeber, precamur,</l>
     <l n="18">Laetior semper redeat, nec ullos</l>
     <l n="19">Hostium motus ferat, aut maligni</l>
     <l n="20">Sideris aestus.</l>
     <l n="21">Da tuis longam, venerande, pacem</l>
     <l n="22">Civibus, da perpetuos honores,</l>
     <l n="23">Da bonam mentem, superique plenos</l>
     <l n="24">Luminis haustus.</l>
     <l n="25">Justa poscentes animos benignus</l>
     <l n="26">Adjuva; injustos moderare sensus.</l>
     <l n="27">Sentiant per te patuisse castis</l>
     <l n="28">Aethera votis.</l>
     <l n="29">Laus tibi, Caeli Pater, atque Princeps,</l>
     <l n="30">Omnium Rector simul et Creator;</l>
     <l n="31">Quem fides veri studiosa Trinum</l>
     <l n="32">Credit, et Unum.</l>
    </lg>
